perhaps use localStorage and/or sessionStorage for storing our data that we need to save, such as user settings
OR use indexedDB which is a clientside database. the indexedDB docs on this url (https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/IndexedDB_API) even say it is too
complex for simple purposes and recommends some alternatives by name so check that out, and this link (https://home.aveek.io/blog/post/get-started-with-svelte/) recommends using this npm module "idb-keyval" which is a simpler wrapper for indexedDB
SEMI-RELATED: there's also https://github.com/robinvdvleuten/vuex-persistedstate which is a vuex plugin that makes sure the vuex datastore keeps its values on page reloads, so you gotta use vuex

